# Diagrams — Mermaid Only

## Rule

**NEVER use SVG files or `![img](*.svg)` references in README files for diagrams.**

**ALWAYS use Mermaid code blocks** (` ```mermaid `) for any diagram.

## What is a diagram

A diagram shows **relationships, flow, or hierarchy** with arrows or connections between elements. Examples: architecture diagrams, data flows, dependency trees, sequence diagrams.

A **catalog of boxes without connections** (a list of items with colors) is NOT a diagram — use a table or bullet list instead.

## Clean commit

When the user says **"commit limpo"**, it means:
1. Erase all git history (orphan branch technique)
2. Single commit with the exact message: `First flight — SWIM CP1 open-source reference architecture`
3. Force push to GitHub
4. Use `git commit-tree` (never `git commit`) to guarantee no Co-authored-by trailer is injected

## Examples

```markdown
❌ WRONG
![Architecture](docs/architecture.svg)

✅ CORRECT
```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[AIXM XSD] -->|generate-sources| B[JAXB / XJC]
    B --> C[SWIM Service]
```
